132
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:56,450
Why would you
be in trouble ?

133
00:07:56,450 --> 00:08:00,450
Well, that's my problem...

134
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:06,150
...but a Road Racer has
to race when challenged.

135
00:08:06,150 --> 00:08:09,450
That might be so if
you're a Road Racer...

136
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:12,320
...but I don't want
to be a Road Racer.

137
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,750
No way.

138
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:18,540
And I don't like the idea that I ``have to'' race when challenged.

139
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:25,150
This is bad.
Extremely bad.

140
00:08:26,150 --> 00:08:27,740
What am I gonna do ?

141
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:46,880
Two more days
till the race.

142
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,870
I'll show that Eight-Six guy
and Takahashi Ryosuke...

143
00:08:50,870 --> 00:08:53,560
...that I'm
number one.

144
00:09:00,780 --> 00:09:01,700
Iketani !

145
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,800
You accepted the match against the Night Kids of Myogi, didn't you ?

146
00:09:07,510 --> 00:09:10,660
If you did something that important,
you should've told the rest of us.

147
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,590
I don't know anything about that.
What're you talking about ?

148
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:18,870
What do you mean ?
Everyone's talking about it.

149
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:21,510
