150
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:25,450
The Eight-Six and...?
Never heard of it.

151
00:09:25,450 --> 00:09:32,100
But they say that Nakazato of the Night Kids came here himself and made the challenge.

152
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:35,730
Takumi, did you
accept his challenge ?

153
00:09:35,730 --> 00:09:37,480
I don't know about it.

154
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,450
No one knows
about it ?

155
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:41,250
That's strange.

156
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,250
I'm sorry.

157
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:48,470
Itsuki, don't tell me...

158
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:52,150
I...I accepted it.

159
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:56,870
I'm sorry !

160
00:09:56,870 --> 00:10:00,870
Nakazato of the Night Kids
came here yesterday.

161
00:10:00,870 --> 00:10:04,830
Neither Iketani nor Takumi
were here at that moment.

162
00:10:04,830 --> 00:10:05,730
I...

163
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:10,990
I was talking to him, pretending to be a member of the Speedstars...

164
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:14,210
...and it just happened.

165
00:10:14,210 --> 00:10:17,770
Why'd you keep something so
important a secret until now ?!

166
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:22,400
I was going to tell you,
but I couldn't find a chance.

167
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,450
I'm sorry, Takumi.

168
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:28,600
Forgive me.
It was my fault.

169
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,020
Even if you say so...

170
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:34,500
Forgive me, forgive me.

171
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,330
Hey, that 32
is here again.

172
00:10:44,330 --> 00:10:47,950
It's gonna race the Eight-Six of the Speedstars tomorrow night, right ?

173
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:50,050
I'll definitely
come and watch.

174
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:50,850
Yeah.

175
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:55,700
Nakazato will challenge the Eight-Six that Takahashi Keisuke couldn't beat.

176
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:57,800
We can't miss it.

177
00:10:58,540 --> 00:11:01,380
It looks like a match between the Speedstars and the Night Kids...

178
00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:02,950
...but in reality...

179
00:11:02,950 --> 00:11:08,080
...it's a clash of pride between the Redsuns' Takahashi brothers and the Night Kids.

180
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:12,800
Whoever wins, Takahashi Ryosuke won't just stand by and watch.

181
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:16,550
Sleepless nights will come one
after another this summer.

182
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:22,800
Anyway, this isn't good.

183
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,600
What should we do ?

184
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:31,350
Since those rumors have spread so widely, we can't withdraw.

185
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:34,830
I'd better ask Takumi
to drive myself.

186
00:11:34,830 --> 00:11:39,900
But even if it's Takumi, we're at a disadvantage because the opponent's a 32.

187
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:45,490
Nakazato of the Night Kids is as famous as the Takahashi brothers.

188
00:11:45,490 --> 00:11:47,450
It's gonna be
a tough battle.

189
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:51,100
It might be a
hopeless battle...

190
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:54,100
...and if I think about it,
I just can't ask him.

191
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,610
We can't.

192
00:12:14,850 --> 00:12:15,800
Here.

193
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:18,930
Hey, Dad...

194
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,980
How good is the 32 ?

195
00:12:21,980 --> 00:12:24,030
The 32 ?

196
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:26,310
It's great.

197
00:12:26,310 --> 00:12:30,600
Could you defeat the 32
on the downhill ?

198
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,650
I'd win.

199
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:36,800
Whether it's a 32 or
not makes no difference.

200
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:41,710
Do you think
I could win ?

201
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:44,020
I don't know.

202
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:47,670
But it'd be
a close match.

203
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:48,800
Why're you
asking me ?

204
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:52,420
Are you going to
race against a 32 ?

205
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:54,000
No reason.

206
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,990
I just wanted to ask.

207
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:58,280
I'm off.

208
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:11,100
So the next
one's a 32.

209
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:14,220
I guess I have to change the settings on the Eight-Six.

210
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:24,780
I don't know, but it'd
be a close match.

211
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:05,160
I had the feeling I'd see you
if I came here at this time.

212
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:08,540
It was about this time
when I first saw you.

213
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:12,250
I heard that you're gonna race against Nakazato of the Night Kids.

214
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:15,500
People are talking about
you all over the place.

215
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:20,130
Let me tell you that
I didn't agree to race him.

216
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:21,150
Say what ?

217
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:27,030
He challenged me while I was away,
and I'm not interested in racing.

218
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:29,990
What do you mean
you're not interested ?

219
00:14:31,420 --> 00:14:36,420
Nakazato of the Night Kids personally challenged you, didn't he ?

220
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:38,230
Why don't you accept ?

221
00:14:38,230 --> 00:14:40,050
And beat the
shit out of him.

222
00:14:40,050 --> 00:14:42,620
You should be
able to do that.

223
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:46,910
Why are you saying that ?
It's none of your business.

224
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:49,050
It sure as hell is...

225
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:51,060
...because you
defeated me.

226
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:58,270
Only the Takahashi brothers of
the Redsuns will defeat you.

227
00:14:58,270 --> 00:15:02,840
Until then, don't lose, even
if it's against the 32.

228
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:05,450
I said I'm
not doing it !

229
00:15:05,450 --> 00:15:07,200
Besides, I don't
have any reason.

230
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,450
Reason ?
What do you mean ?

231
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,400
Why does a Road Racer
need a reason to race ?

232
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:16,060
I'm not a Road Racer.

233
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:17,450
Stop screwing
around with me !

234
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:20,980
Are you trying
to be sarcastic ?

235
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:25,570
You must've been driving a lot
to acquire such great technique.

236
00:15:25,570 --> 00:15:29,030
Why would someone other than a Road Racer drive so much ?

237
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:31,720
I don't mean to drive that
way because I want to.

238
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:34,500
I have to drive
to help the shop.

239
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,050
Don't lie to me.

240
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:40,720
How can you learn such great technique if you drive unwillingly ?

241
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,760
That's not it.

242
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:44,070
You don't understand.

243
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:46,940
You're the one who
doesn't understand !

244
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:50,870
How could someone who
hates driving master drift ?

245
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:55,060
Only those who like to drive can master that kind of technique.

246
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:58,060
You might not
have noticed...

247
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:01,140
...but you like to
drive in your heart.

248
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:06,710
Listen, if you like to drive a car, that's enough to be called a Road Racer.

249
00:16:06,710 --> 00:16:11,610
If you're a Road Racer, you should have pride in the techniques you've learned.

250
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:13,450
If someone challenges you,
you accept it.

251
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:15,450
That's the pride
of a Road Racer.

252
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:19,100
I'm disappointed
I came to see you.

253
00:16:37,990 --> 00:16:41,170
I hadn't realized...

254
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:43,800
...that I like
to drive a car ?

255
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:51,660
But that doesn't mean I ``must'' accept someone's challenge.

256
00:16:52,890 --> 00:16:55,080
I just don't get it.

257
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:59,070
Hey, Itsuki,
where's Takumi ?

258
00:16:59,070 --> 00:17:01,000
He's on late
shift today.

259
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,000
I see.

260
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:04,580
Iketani.

261
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:11,590
I'll go to Mt. Akina tonight and apologize to Nakazato of the Night Kids.

262
00:17:11,590 --> 00:17:13,440
Itsuki...

263
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:17,600
If I beg him, and explain what happened, he might understand.

264
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:22,190
Originally, it had nothing
to do with the Speedstars.

265
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:25,750
I wonder if there's
a way to convince Takumi.

266
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:29,830
I don't think it's possible.
I know him too well.

267
00:17:29,830 --> 00:17:35,700
He really hates it when someone tries to force or order him around.

268
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:42,150
He looks quiet, but once he makes up his mind, he gets stubborn and won't change it.

269
00:17:42,150 --> 00:17:46,200
That part of his personality
is identical to his father's.

270
00:17:46,870 --> 00:17:51,100
He doesn't like the idea of accepting someone's challenge automatically.

271
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:54,450
That's why he's resisting.

272
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:57,420
If we force him,
he'll get mad.

273
00:17:57,420 --> 00:18:02,710
When he was a sophomore, he got pissed, and beat up a senior in the soccer club.

274
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:04,450
Takumi did ?

275
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:21,890
Manager, I'm finished outside.

276
00:18:21,890 --> 00:18:23,750
Good work.

277
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:26,300
Well then,
I'm heading home.

278
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,830
Takumi.

279
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,470
Sit down over here
for a sec.

280
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:39,820
I heard a rumor that you're
going to race a 32 tonight.

281
00:18:41,130 --> 00:18:41,990
Well, I...

282
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:45,450
You'd better not, because
that's a tough opponent.

283
00:18:45,450 --> 00:18:47,560
Well, about that...

284
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,000
Don't say anything.

285
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,620
I understand without
you telling me.

286
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:54,130
I know all about it.

287
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:58,550
I know that you didn't
accept the battle.

288
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:01,100
Itsuki accepted it without
asking, didn't he ?

289
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,120
Yeah.

290
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:04,890
But you're too nice.

291
00:19:04,890 --> 00:19:08,550
You don't have to save
face for your friend.

292
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:11,750
I'm telling you. You'd better stay away from the 32.

293
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:14,250
You don't know
much about cars...

294
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:17,250
...so you don't know what kind
of car the 32 is, do you ?

295
00:19:18,050 --> 00:19:21,380
Is a 32
that good ?

296
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:26,650
Good, he took the bait.

297
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:29,050
It's far
better than good.

298
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:31,020
It's totally overwhelming.

299
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:35,790
It's got a drive train that combines the advantages of both FR and 4WD.

300
00:19:35,790 --> 00:19:37,870
It's so unfair.

301
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:41,790
The GT-R is totally different from the Eight-Six.

302
00:19:41,790 --> 00:19:44,100
Maybe if the
driver wasn't good...

303
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,790
But your opponent is a
famous Road Racer, isn't he ?

304
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:49,350
It's different
from what Dad said.

305
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:52,300
He said it would
be a close match.

306
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:53,860
Hey...

307
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,500
Are you listening ?

308
00:19:55,500 --> 00:20:00,270
You got famous by defeating
the team from Akagi.

309
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:02,870
You should keep it.

310
00:20:02,870 --> 00:20:06,810
It's not wise to race against someone you have no chance of beating.

311
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:08,710
Right, Takumi ?

312
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:13,130
The opponent is a 32, so even if you don't race, no one will think you ran away.

313
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,540
Run away ?!

314
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:20,700
Manager...

315
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:25,870
...thanks for
your advice.

316
00:20:25,870 --> 00:20:31,100
I don't think it's important to gain fame as a Road Racer at all.

317
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:37,990
So you're not
gonna quit.

318
00:20:37,990 --> 00:20:39,960
I won't.

319
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:43,000
Having heard how
good it is...

320
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,570
...I want to see how
good it is myself.

321
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:52,850
I'm not afraid
of the 32.

322
00:20:52,850 --> 00:20:53,850
Excuse me.

323
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:03,800
His reaction is surprisingly similar to his father's.

324
00:21:08,580 --> 00:21:10,450
Temporarily closed due
to private reasons.
Fujiwara Tofu Shop

325
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:13,010
Temporarily closed ?

326
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:16,300
I hadn't heard anything.

327
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:19,790
We're poor, so he
should be working.

328
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:21,860
Damn, the car.

329
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:28,200
If he's gone out drinking,
it's hopeless.

330
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:31,180
That shitty old man won't
come home until morning.

331
00:21:32,390 --> 00:21:35,060
If I don't have a car,
I can't go anywhere.

332
00:21:35,060 --> 00:21:37,840
I should've asked
him this morning.

333
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,330
The galleries
are really packed.

334
00:21:42,330 --> 00:21:46,000
There are more people this time than there were during the race against the Akagi team.

335
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:49,840
What did they
come to see ?

336
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:52,580
I'll bet it's
not the 32.

337
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:55,360
Of course, it's the drift
of the Eight-Six.

338
00:21:55,360 --> 00:22:00,350
He keeps the gas pedal open one corner after another, and they say he's so fast.

339
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:02,840
I can't wait
to see it.

340
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:07,050
Oh, I see.

341
00:22:07,050 --> 00:22:12,960
If he shows up, could you
tell him to call home ?

342
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:14,330
Thank you.

343
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:21,340
It's no use.
I can't find him.

344
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:22,100
Shit.

345
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,390
You stupid old man !
Bring back the Eight-Six !

346
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,920
My pride says "You gotta be wild and tough."
